The paper deals with the non-stationarity of wireless channels, which is a topic commonly studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) communities. The use of algorithms specific to channel estimation and beamforming suggests a systems (cs.SY) perspective. The paper also involves measurements and analysis of data, which could fall under multimedia (cs.MM) or mobile computing (cs.MA).
